      "content": "idk i feel like there's a difference in how these things are described depending on what the group is actually protesting for. like if it was a group of business owners or something downtown, people would probably call it an \"organized demonstration\" or a \"rally\" even with some noise. but with this crowd, since it's about civil rights and stuff, everyone seems to jump straight to \"unrest\" or \"clashes\" almost automatically. do u think the language used to describe these events changes based on the demographic of the people protesting?",
